## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-prior-auths
instruction: Click "Prior Authorizations" in the main sidebar under "My Workspace."
success_criteria: You are on the Prior Authorizations page with a "Create PA" button in the top-right corner.
anchor: "Prior Authorizations"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The link is in the left sidebar under "My Workspace."

### step 2
id: click-create-pa
instruction: Click the "Create PA" button.
success_criteria: Step 1 of the PA wizard is open with fields for Patient, Billing Account, and Rendering Provider.
anchor: "Create PA"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The button is in the top-right corner.

### step 3
id: select-patient
instruction: Search for and select the patient. Type their name in the Patient field and select the correct result.
success_criteria: A patient is selected and their name is displayed.
anchor: "Patient"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click the Patient field and start typing the name. Select from the dropdown.

### step 4
id: select-account-and-provider
instruction: Select the Billing Account (provider NPI) and Rendering Provider from their respective dropdowns. Then click "Next."
success_criteria: Both are selected and Step 2 of the wizard is open showing fields for Payer, Procedure Codes, Diagnosis Codes, Linked Visit, and Supporting Documents.
anchor: "Next"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click each dropdown and select the appropriate option. Then click Next.

### step 5
id: enter-authorization-details
instruction: Fill in the authorization details:
  - **Payer**: search for and select the patient's insurance company
  - **Procedure Codes**: add the CPT/HCPCS codes requiring authorization, with unit counts (at least one required)
  - **Diagnosis Codes**: optionally add ICD-10 codes to support medical necessity
  - **Linked Visit**: optionally link to a scheduled encounter
  - **Supporting Documents**: optionally attach clinical notes or referral letters (PDF, images up to 10MB each)
success_criteria: All required fields are filled. At least one procedure code with units is entered.
anchor: "Payer"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Each field has search functionality — start typing and select from results.

### step 6
id: review-pa
instruction: Click "Next" to go to the Review & Submit step. Verify all details: patient, account, provider, payer, procedure codes, diagnosis codes, and documents.
success_criteria: You are on the Review & Submit step and all details look correct.
anchor: "Next"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click the Next button to reach the review step.

### step 7
id: submit-pa
instruction: Click "Submit to Altair" to create and submit the prior authorization.
success_criteria: The PA has been created. You are on the PA detail page showing the PA ID and initial status.
anchor: "Submit to Altair"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Make sure all required fields are correct. Click the submit button.

## Completion Message
prior auth created! altair is tracking it and will help you follow up with the payer. check the PA detail page for status updates — once approved, you'll see the authorization number and approved units there.

